[{"id":"FT581297","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>Which of the following would most directly challenge the labor system portrayed in the sketch?</p>","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"text-center\"><strong>A SKETCH BY JAN BRANDES, DUTCH LUTHERAN MINISTER LIVING IN JAKARTA, INDONESIA, 1784</strong></p>\n\n<p class=\"text-center\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a sketch titled “A Sketch by Jan Brandes, Dutch Lutheran Minister Living in Jakarta, Indonesia, 1784.” The sketch depicts the inside of a home. All of the windows in the home are open, and there are birds on perches near each wall. A young boy, who is the artist’s son Johnny, is shown in the center of the sketch, holding an open book. He is dressed in traditional Dutch clothing. An enslaved Indonesian woman named Flora is shown on the right side of the sketch, pulling thread through a spinning wheel. She is dressed in traditional Indonesian clothing.\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/3b4e1c99523ad489a24d52582c48e31d/original.jpg\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:0.9em\">Rijksmuseum, Amsterdam, The Netherlands / Bridgeman Images</span></p>\n\n<p><em>The sketch shows the artist’s son Johnny and Flora, an enslaved Indonesian household servant.</em></p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p>Trade unionism</p>","<p>The Enlightenment</p>","<p>Social Darwinism</p>","<p>Marxism</p>"],"answer":0}]